node.title: Gladys Berejiklian rules out running for federal seat of Warringah
node.description: Former NSW premier Gladys Berejiklian rules herself out of the running for the federal seat of Warringah.
node.content: ["Former NSW premier Gladys Berejiklian has ruled herself out of the running for the federal seat of Warringah.\u00a0", "Ms Berejiklian told Nine radio she would be moving into the private sector.", "\"I'm looking forward to a much less public life,\" she said.", "\"I won't be contesting the seat of Warringah, or any other seat for that matter.", "\"I'm going into another different direction and I'm looking forward to the opportunities next year brings.\"", "Ms Berejiklian quit politics in October after it was revealed she was the subject of an investigation by the state\u2019s corruption watchdog.\u00a0", "The Independent Commission Against Corruption (ICAC) is probing her dealings with her disgraced former boyfriend and former Wagga Wagga MP Daryl Maguire.\u00a0", "More to come."]
